WEBVTT

00:00.399 --> 00:02.069
Man:
All you have as a cop
is other cops.

00:02.322 --> 00:03.223
But we walked away.

00:03.256 --> 00:05.158
Woman #1:
We all thought he was guilty.

00:05.191 --> 00:06.927
Woman #2:
After the trial,
I had to get counseling

00:06.960 --> 00:08.862
just so I could sleep.

00:08.895 --> 00:10.764
Woman #1:
There was all that proof.

00:10.797 --> 00:13.233
Man:
We all turned our back
on Charlie Crews.

00:13.266 --> 00:16.102
In his first years,

00:16.136 --> 00:20.240
he was in that prison hospital

00:20.273 --> 00:21.307
more--
more than he was out.

00:21.341 --> 00:24.344
[Grunting]

00:25.912 --> 00:27.748
Cop doing time, please.

00:27.781 --> 00:29.349
Broke nearly every bone
in his body.

00:29.382 --> 00:30.784
[Grunting]

00:30.817 --> 00:32.819
I heard they cut him
real bad too.

00:32.853 --> 00:33.720
Over 100 stitches.

00:33.754 --> 00:35.856
About 241 stitches.

00:38.759 --> 00:40.694
Woman:
I mean, the jury was only out
for an hour.

00:40.727 --> 00:41.527
There was all that proof.

00:41.561 --> 00:43.830
Man:
After the case was reopened,

00:43.864 --> 00:46.299
we found that none
of the physical evidence

00:46.332 --> 00:49.302
on scene matched Officer Crews.

00:49.335 --> 00:50.837
Woman:
I wasn't the only one.

00:50.871 --> 00:53.039
We all thought he was guilty.

00:53.073 --> 00:54.708
Male interviewer:
Did Charlie tell you
he didn't do it?

00:54.741 --> 00:56.209
Yes.

00:56.242 --> 00:57.811
Interviewer:
And how did you feel
when you found out

00:57.844 --> 00:59.112
he was being exonerated?

00:59.145 --> 01:01.214
That he was innocent?

01:06.386 --> 01:09.790
I don't wanna do this anymore.

01:09.823 --> 01:10.824
[Grunts]

01:13.760 --> 01:14.594
As I said
at the press conference

01:14.627 --> 01:16.229
after Detective Crews
was exonerated,

01:16.262 --> 01:18.999
life was his sentence,

01:19.032 --> 01:21.702
and life is what he got back.

01:32.345 --> 01:34.981
Reese:
Crews!

01:35.015 --> 01:37.217
Detective Crews!

01:37.250 --> 01:38.418
Detective Crews!

01:38.451 --> 01:41.054
You are Detective Crews,
aren't you?

01:41.087 --> 01:43.056
Yeah.

01:43.089 --> 01:45.158
I guess I am.

01:45.191 --> 01:46.960
Okay, well, would you like
to be sure?

01:46.993 --> 01:48.995
Because we're about
to walk into a crime scene.

01:49.029 --> 01:51.097
I'm sure.

01:51.131 --> 01:53.666
Great.

01:57.938 --> 01:59.039
Are you Reese?

01:59.072 --> 02:01.742
Detective Reese.

02:03.376 --> 02:05.211
Woman:
Uh-huh.

02:05.245 --> 02:06.679
10-4.

02:16.823 --> 02:18.959
Crews, it's a kid in there.

02:18.992 --> 02:20.426
It's your first day back.

02:20.460 --> 02:22.929
If you don't think you can
handle it, I can do it myself.

02:33.206 --> 02:36.142
[Heavy sigh]

02:51.191 --> 02:54.795
Small caliber, close range.
Probably not a lot of noise.

02:54.828 --> 02:56.396
No one reported
hearing anything.

02:56.429 --> 03:00.133
The bullet was
a through and through.

03:00.516 --> 03:01.484
Is that the kid's dog?

03:01.517 --> 03:02.418
Yeah, he won't move.

03:02.452 --> 03:05.221
Reese:
Did you find the slug?

03:05.255 --> 03:06.222
Zerco:
No, ma'am.

03:06.256 --> 03:08.158
Did you look for it?

03:08.191 --> 03:10.626
Yes, detective.
We looked for it.

03:10.660 --> 03:13.596
Did you ask the dog?

03:13.629 --> 03:14.630
Zerco:
Did we ask the dog?

03:14.664 --> 03:15.365
Krebbs:
We did not ask the dog, no.

03:15.398 --> 03:19.135
No, sir.
We did not ask the dog.

03:27.910 --> 03:29.845
Hey. Shh.

03:29.879 --> 03:31.647
Hey.

03:31.681 --> 03:33.649
Hey. Hey.

03:38.754 --> 03:40.890
[Softly]
Good boy.

03:40.923 --> 03:42.592
[Whispering to dog]

03:45.828 --> 03:48.598
There's a bullet here
beneath the skin.

03:48.631 --> 03:50.700
Dog must have caught the bullet
in the gut

03:50.733 --> 03:52.202
after it exited the kid.

03:52.235 --> 03:54.570
All right,
get the dog to a vet.

03:54.604 --> 03:57.473
Get the bullet out
and to ballistics.

03:57.507 --> 03:59.542
What are you doing way
over here?

03:59.575 --> 04:01.311
Krebbs:
Get me animal reg
to my location.

04:01.344 --> 04:02.478
Did you bring something over?

04:02.512 --> 04:05.315
Your master's over there.

04:08.751 --> 04:11.587
Did you bring something over?
Huh?

04:11.621 --> 04:14.457
Reese:
Detective Crews.

04:14.490 --> 04:16.892
Detective!

04:16.926 --> 04:19.329
Zerco:
Hey, hold on.

04:19.362 --> 04:20.796
That looks like a--

04:20.830 --> 04:21.964
is that a finger?

04:21.997 --> 04:23.699
Yeah.

04:34.544 --> 04:36.512
Dog must have took a bullet
for the kid,

04:36.546 --> 04:39.782
then took
the shooter's finger off.

04:39.815 --> 04:41.817
Anyone ever love you
that much?

04:49.859 --> 04:50.760
If I got out
after all that time,

04:50.793 --> 04:52.395
I got all that money,
I sure as [bleep]

04:52.428 --> 04:53.896
Would not be going
back to work.

04:53.929 --> 04:56.499
Now I handle
his settlement money.

04:56.532 --> 04:57.900
Interviewer:
And how much would that be?

04:57.933 --> 05:01.671
That's undisclosed
by court order.

05:01.704 --> 05:03.873
Interviewer:
And what about details
of the settlement?

05:03.906 --> 05:06.776
I'm not at liberty to say.

05:06.809 --> 05:08.278
Yeah, I-I heard he got
$5 million.

05:08.311 --> 05:09.412
Can--can I say [bleep]?

05:09.445 --> 05:11.247
5?
I heard it was 50.

05:13.283 --> 05:14.850
So you wanna have
the talk?

05:14.884 --> 05:16.852
Which talk is that?

05:16.886 --> 05:18.554
About how you didn't want me
as your partner,

05:18.588 --> 05:19.555
and you're looking
to transfer out

05:19.589 --> 05:20.856
as soon as you can.

05:20.890 --> 05:23.726
Nope.
I don't wanna have that talk.

05:23.759 --> 05:25.628
You wanna have the talk
about what you did?

05:25.661 --> 05:26.896
Who you pissed off to get
partnered up with me?

05:26.929 --> 05:29.499
I was handed a slip of paper.
It said you're my new partner.

05:29.532 --> 05:30.666
It didn't mention why,
and I didn't ask.

05:30.700 --> 05:32.835
Getting stuck with me isn't
exactly a promotion for you.

05:32.868 --> 05:34.804
Detective, it might be a habit
of yours, but I don't wanna have

05:34.837 --> 05:36.939
the "what are you in for"
talk either.

05:36.972 --> 05:39.775
Not a big talker.

05:39.809 --> 05:42.612
See, I've learned something
about you already.

05:42.645 --> 05:45.948
John was not my biological son.

05:45.981 --> 05:47.917
He was Alyssa's
from her first marriage.

05:47.950 --> 05:50.853
We have another one
of our own,

05:50.886 --> 05:51.787
a daughter.

05:51.821 --> 05:54.690
You adopted John?

05:54.724 --> 05:56.058
Yeah, I always think
of him as my own.

05:56.091 --> 05:59.061
As a member of the family.

05:59.094 --> 06:01.864
I thought of--
thought of him as...

06:04.099 --> 06:06.736
Where is John's
biological father?

06:06.769 --> 06:07.937
Jail.

06:07.970 --> 06:09.972
He's, uh...

06:10.005 --> 06:13.609
Possession
with intent to distribute.

06:13.643 --> 06:15.711
He's got ten more years.

06:18.047 --> 06:19.649
The--the Scout troop

06:19.682 --> 06:21.717
that John is a--

06:21.751 --> 06:24.687
was a part of
is made up entirely

06:24.720 --> 06:28.758
of boys who have fathers
who are doing time.

06:28.791 --> 06:30.960
All right,
we're almost through.

06:30.993 --> 06:32.528
You reported
a break-in last month?

06:32.562 --> 06:34.564
Yeah, um.

06:34.597 --> 06:35.365
[Clears throat]

06:35.398 --> 06:37.733
Some cash and jewelry
was taken.

06:37.767 --> 06:38.868
No one was caught.

06:38.901 --> 06:41.704
We changed the locks
and the alarms.

06:41.737 --> 06:42.705
Makes me paranoid.

06:42.738 --> 06:43.739
I--what?
I don't understand.

06:43.773 --> 06:44.740
Pot.

06:44.774 --> 06:47.843
Just makes me, you know,
overprocess everything.

06:47.877 --> 06:50.045
I end up spinning myself
into a freak-out.

06:50.229 --> 06:51.864
You get high today, Warren?

06:51.897 --> 06:53.599
Yeah?
It's Sunday.

06:53.633 --> 06:54.934
A little wake and bake?
Huh?

06:54.967 --> 06:56.101
Because in the next few hours,

06:56.135 --> 06:57.637
there's gonna be all kinds
of law enforcement

06:57.670 --> 06:58.638
crawling all over
your beautiful house.

06:58.671 --> 06:59.605
Detective.

06:59.639 --> 07:01.841
They turn up a bag
of high-grade chronic, well,

07:01.874 --> 07:03.275
I think you need to be here
for your family today--

07:03.308 --> 07:04.276
detective.
And you do not--

07:04.309 --> 07:05.778
Detective!

07:05.811 --> 07:06.912
May I speak with you?

07:06.946 --> 07:08.080
Sure thing.

07:08.113 --> 07:09.515
[Whispers]
Why don't you go
to the bathroom?

07:09.549 --> 07:11.216
When you're done,
make sure you flush real well.

07:11.250 --> 07:13.686
Okay?
You know, maybe flush twice.

07:13.719 --> 07:15.688
You understand?

07:17.823 --> 07:19.859
Excuse me.

07:21.727 --> 07:22.895
What the hell was that?

07:22.928 --> 07:24.196
What, you wanna see
the dead boy's dad

07:24.229 --> 07:25.865
get locked up for holding
a little hay?

07:25.898 --> 07:27.967
Stepdad, and a possible suspect
in a murder--

07:28.000 --> 07:29.802
in a child murder.

07:29.835 --> 07:31.303
That man didn't kill anyone,
and you know it.

07:31.336 --> 07:33.539
He's got all his fingers,
and he seemed really sad.

07:33.573 --> 07:34.807
You just broke the law.

07:34.840 --> 07:36.008
I am your superior detective.

07:36.041 --> 07:37.577
I'm responsible
for your actions.

07:37.610 --> 07:39.178
If you get jammed up for this,
I get jammed up for this.

07:39.211 --> 07:41.046
Hey, we're both
adults here.

07:41.080 --> 07:43.148
You got a problem,
turn me over to the rat squad.

07:43.182 --> 07:45.117
[Cell phone ringing]

07:49.889 --> 07:51.190
Are you gonna get that?

07:51.223 --> 07:52.625
Oh.

07:52.658 --> 07:54.293
A phone this small
in your pocket.

07:54.326 --> 07:55.861
It's science fiction,
right?

07:55.895 --> 07:58.030
This living
in the future--

08:01.934 --> 08:04.970
Reese:
Was John having trouble
in school?

08:05.004 --> 08:05.871
Alyssa:
No.

08:05.905 --> 08:07.106
Reese:
In the neighborhood?

08:07.139 --> 08:08.340
Alyssa:
No.

08:08.373 --> 08:11.611
Other kids in the scout troop?

08:11.644 --> 08:12.912
What about the break-in?

08:12.945 --> 08:14.680
He was with me
when that happened.

08:14.714 --> 08:15.948
John had nothing
to do with that.

08:15.981 --> 08:17.983
I wasn't
suggesting that, ma'am.

08:18.017 --> 08:20.285
No, I'm sorry.
Of course you weren't.

08:20.319 --> 08:22.054
We're gonna need
to ask you a few questions

08:22.087 --> 08:23.756
about your ex-husband mark.

08:32.131 --> 08:35.300
Mark wasn't a bad man
when I married him.

08:35.334 --> 08:36.501
He had a problem with drugs.

08:36.535 --> 08:39.805
But when he came out of jail
the first time, he'd changed.

08:39.839 --> 08:42.742
He was mean.

08:42.775 --> 08:45.210
When he went back in,
I knew I had to get away.

08:45.244 --> 08:49.281
So you just dumped
the divorce papers in the mail.

08:49.314 --> 08:50.616
What did you just say?

08:50.650 --> 08:51.717
What'd you just say?

08:51.751 --> 08:54.954
What?

08:54.987 --> 08:58.991
What did I just say?

08:59.024 --> 09:00.359
Two of the other dads
in the Scout troop have records

09:00.392 --> 09:02.361
of violence against children,

09:02.394 --> 09:05.230
but both those dads
are in jail.

09:05.264 --> 09:07.967
I'm gonna call in,
see if they got a hit

09:08.000 --> 09:09.134
off that finger we found.

09:09.168 --> 09:10.703
It was
pretty chewed up, but...

09:10.736 --> 09:13.673
Okay, okay.
You're mad at me.

09:13.706 --> 09:15.274
Mad? No, I'm not mad.

09:15.307 --> 09:17.677
I mean, I don't even think
there is a word for what I am.

09:17.710 --> 09:20.212
What you did to that husband,
I kinda get, okay?

09:20.245 --> 09:21.380
I mean, I guess I kind of get,

09:21.413 --> 09:22.648
but what you said
to that wife--

09:22.682 --> 09:24.917
I know.
That one was me.

09:24.950 --> 09:27.119
It was my fault.
I take responsibility, Reese.

09:27.152 --> 09:29.755
I wasn't in the moment.

09:29.789 --> 09:31.691
If I had stayed in the moment,
if I had stayed present,

09:31.724 --> 09:34.126
I would have been okay,
but I didn't.

09:34.159 --> 09:36.295
I was thinking
about where we're going next.

09:36.328 --> 09:38.063
So I left the moment
just when I should have been

09:38.097 --> 09:39.832
completely in the moment,
which is when people

09:39.865 --> 09:41.266
usually leave the moment
because the moment is just

09:41.300 --> 09:43.435
too much for her.

09:43.468 --> 09:46.806
I mean, the moment is pretty
much always too much, you know?

09:50.042 --> 09:53.879
I was thinking
about where we're going next.

09:57.349 --> 09:59.018
Must feel good to come in

09:59.051 --> 10:02.221
without a cavity search.
Right, detective?

10:02.254 --> 10:04.389
'Course, you want one
for old times' sake,

10:04.423 --> 10:05.958
we could work something out.

10:05.991 --> 10:07.827
Just take us
to Rawls, okay?

10:07.860 --> 10:09.695
Sure thing, sweetheart.

10:31.951 --> 10:34.720
They won't let me go
to his funeral.

10:34.754 --> 10:37.489
My own son's funeral.

10:37.522 --> 10:38.758
Mr. Rawls, I'd like
for you to think and see

10:38.791 --> 10:39.925
if you can help us.

10:39.959 --> 10:42.795
They won't let me go
to my son's funeral.

10:42.828 --> 10:44.396
Why don't you help me?

10:44.429 --> 10:45.765
You do not
raise your voice to her.

10:45.798 --> 10:49.268
I want to do more than raise
my voice to her.

10:49.301 --> 10:50.335
You gonna stop me?

10:50.369 --> 10:53.906
Do you hate cops?

10:53.939 --> 10:57.076
Oh, yeah.

10:57.109 --> 10:59.078
Well, I hate cops too.

11:02.848 --> 11:05.284
Mr. Rawls, have you made
any enemies here in prison

11:05.317 --> 11:06.085
that would want
to hurt your family?

11:06.118 --> 11:10.422
Get back at you
by killing your son?

11:10.455 --> 11:13.358
Rawls:
Yeah, I got enemies.

11:13.392 --> 11:14.760
But none
that would touch my son.

11:14.794 --> 11:16.195
Why is that?

11:16.228 --> 11:19.064
Because everyone's got family.

11:19.098 --> 11:22.935
That's right.

11:22.968 --> 11:26.005
Everyone.

11:26.038 --> 11:27.306
Mr. Rawls, you last saw John
two weeks ago

11:27.339 --> 11:28.407
when the Scout troop came.

11:28.440 --> 11:31.210
How did he seem to you?
Was he in any kind of trouble?

11:31.243 --> 11:35.147
Last time I saw John,
he kept saying

11:35.180 --> 11:38.317
how he thought
I shouldn't be here.

11:38.350 --> 11:41.320
It's like he needed
to believe it.

11:45.224 --> 11:46.892
Reese:
No threats against his family.

11:47.076 --> 11:49.111
C.O. #2:
Not that we know,
but we just work here.

11:49.144 --> 11:50.479
We go home after our shifts.

11:50.512 --> 11:52.281
It's the convicts
who are here 24/7

11:52.314 --> 11:53.282
that know
what really goes on.

11:53.465 --> 11:54.599
He means inmates.

11:54.633 --> 11:55.800
He means convicts.

11:55.834 --> 11:57.802
What?
You don't like that word?

11:57.836 --> 11:58.837
What do you care?

12:01.473 --> 12:02.374
Come on, Crews.
Let's go.

12:02.407 --> 12:03.558
Yeah, we know
who you are.

12:03.558 --> 12:05.160
We know you did
your 12 years.

12:05.194 --> 12:08.063
Maybe you were innocent.
Maybe not.

12:08.097 --> 12:09.464
It don't make
no difference to us

12:09.498 --> 12:10.465
because we know
what you did

12:10.499 --> 12:11.733
to that correctional officer

12:11.766 --> 12:13.368
up in Pelican Bay,
and that makes you a con.

12:13.402 --> 12:15.370
Don't it?

12:15.554 --> 12:17.289
You two need
to escort us out now.

12:17.322 --> 12:21.460
You getting angry,
convict?

12:21.493 --> 12:25.430
Anger ruins joy,
steals the goodness of my mind,

12:25.464 --> 12:27.499
forces my mouth
to say terrible things.

12:27.532 --> 12:29.668
Overcoming anger
brings peace of mind,

12:29.701 --> 12:31.336
leads to a mind
without regrets.

12:31.370 --> 12:33.838
If I overcome anger,
I will be delightful

12:33.872 --> 12:35.274
and loved by everyone.

12:35.307 --> 12:37.242
Are you making fun
of us?

12:37.276 --> 12:40.745
It is the universe
that makes fun of us all.

12:48.720 --> 12:52.457
Why exactly would the universe
make fun of us all?

12:52.491 --> 12:54.759
Maybe it's insecure.

12:54.793 --> 12:58.430
[Man on car stereo]
To detach your feelings
from the event.

12:58.463 --> 13:02.667
To detach your feelings
from the object.

13:02.701 --> 13:04.536
I am not attached
to this car.

13:05.970 --> 13:08.407
I am not attached to this car.

13:08.440 --> 13:11.176
[Rock music]

13:11.210 --> 13:15.547
I'm just a little attached
to this car.

13:15.580 --> 13:17.749
Ha ha ha!

13:17.782 --> 13:25.824
♫

13:38.270 --> 13:39.271
So what is it this time?

13:39.304 --> 13:41.306
License
and registration.

13:41.340 --> 13:43.308
You know damn well
who I am.

13:43.342 --> 13:45.210
License
and registration, please.

13:45.244 --> 13:47.546
Look, I married your ex-wife.

13:47.579 --> 13:49.281
That is not a crime.

13:49.314 --> 13:50.582
Are you aware
that you changed lanes

13:50.615 --> 13:52.751
back there without signaling?

13:52.784 --> 13:55.320
You have nothing better
to do?

13:55.354 --> 13:56.888
No, sir.

13:56.921 --> 13:58.923
Not at this moment.

14:03.594 --> 14:05.596
We're talking to everyone in
John's Scout troop, okay, Tyler?

14:05.629 --> 14:06.864
Yes, ma'am.

14:06.897 --> 14:08.699
Some of the other boys said

14:08.732 --> 14:10.834
that you and John were close,
is that right?

14:10.868 --> 14:12.403
Yeah.
I suppose.

14:12.436 --> 14:14.405
Tyler, lift your head up
when you speak.

14:14.438 --> 14:16.240
Ah, mushy.

14:16.274 --> 14:17.375
Did John ever talk
to you

14:17.408 --> 14:18.642
about any problems
he was having?

14:18.676 --> 14:20.544
Were there any new people
in his life?

14:20.578 --> 14:21.512
No, ma'am.

14:21.545 --> 14:22.513
That's the one.

14:22.546 --> 14:23.781
Green Anjou.

14:23.814 --> 14:26.350
You know, some people
are allergic to pears.

14:26.384 --> 14:27.851
Gives them a rash.
Not me though.

14:27.885 --> 14:30.154
Tyler.

14:30.188 --> 14:33.424
Was John
in any sort of trouble?

14:33.457 --> 14:34.758
Grandmother:
Don't lie
to this woman, Tyler.

14:34.792 --> 14:36.126
I'm not lying.

14:39.430 --> 14:42.166
Reese, I guess
what I wanna say is

14:42.200 --> 14:44.335
you've probably had
to fight,

14:44.368 --> 14:45.603
being a woman
in this department.

14:45.636 --> 14:46.904
Had to fight a lot, right?

14:46.937 --> 14:47.805
Fight for everything
you ever got?

14:47.838 --> 14:49.740
Detective Crews,
this is not

14:49.773 --> 14:51.509
the place for that discussion.

14:51.542 --> 14:52.510
Detective Crews!

14:52.543 --> 14:53.844
I just wanted to s--
Crews.

14:53.877 --> 14:55.613
I just wanted
to let you know that--
Step back.

14:55.646 --> 14:57.681
You don't have
to fight with me.
Step back.

14:57.715 --> 14:59.783
She thinks
I'm gonna hug her.

14:59.817 --> 15:01.519
You think
I'm gonna hug you.

15:01.552 --> 15:02.720
[Laughs]
As I hug my partner

15:02.753 --> 15:04.688
I know she is real.

15:04.722 --> 15:06.624
I mindfully meet this person
with open arms

15:06.657 --> 15:07.658
and an open heart.

15:07.691 --> 15:10.628
[Laughter]

15:10.661 --> 15:13.397
I'm not gonna fight
with you, I won't.

15:13.431 --> 15:14.732
You don't wanna hold it
in anymore,

15:14.765 --> 15:16.467
do you, Tyler?

15:16.500 --> 15:18.936
What you know
about what happened to John.

15:18.969 --> 15:22.406
Something's inside you,
but you wanna let it out.

15:22.440 --> 15:23.674
You don't wanna hold it
in any longer.

15:23.707 --> 15:25.743
You can't hold it in.

15:28.746 --> 15:31.315
What is it, Tyler?

15:34.785 --> 15:36.754
Some man--

15:36.787 --> 15:38.689
some man offered
to sell John information

15:39.622 --> 15:41.224
about his dad's case.

15:41.258 --> 15:44.494
About a technicality
in the arrest.

15:44.527 --> 15:47.497
He said that he could get
his dad out of jail.

15:47.530 --> 15:49.232
Who was it?

15:49.266 --> 15:51.234
I don't know.

15:51.268 --> 15:52.569
Grandmother:
Tell them who this man was!

15:52.602 --> 15:54.504
I don't know!

15:54.537 --> 15:55.638
We met him online.

15:55.672 --> 15:58.475
He sent John an I.M.

15:58.508 --> 15:59.742
I don't know who he really is.

15:59.776 --> 16:01.711
An I.M.
He sent John an I.M.

16:01.744 --> 16:02.879
He sent John an I.M.

16:02.912 --> 16:04.514
Oh, my God!

16:04.547 --> 16:06.649
Why would you talk
to some man online?

16:06.683 --> 16:08.418
Well, he knew all
about his dad's case.

16:08.451 --> 16:09.886
He said he was a lawyer.

16:09.919 --> 16:14.657
John believed him?

16:14.691 --> 16:16.593
He said if John paid,
he'd get stuff

16:16.626 --> 16:18.595
to show it was
a bad arrest.

16:18.628 --> 16:21.398
He just wanted
to get his dad out.

16:21.431 --> 16:22.565
John just wanted
to get his dad

16:22.599 --> 16:27.837
out of jail,
and now he's dead.

16:27.870 --> 16:29.539
I should have told somebody.

16:29.572 --> 16:31.608
If I had told somebody,
maybe...

16:31.641 --> 16:35.278
Come here.

16:38.481 --> 16:41.618
Reese, what exactly is an I.M.?

16:45.888 --> 16:49.292
What is it?
An email?

16:49.326 --> 16:52.195
Man:
Is that
detective Charlie Crews?

16:52.229 --> 16:54.297
You know, I thought it was you,

16:54.331 --> 16:55.965
but I was kinda blinded
by the glint

16:55.998 --> 16:57.467
off that detective badge.

16:57.500 --> 16:59.336
Dani Reese, Bobby Stark.

16:59.369 --> 17:04.574
No.
Are you Charlie's new partner?

17:04.607 --> 17:06.276
We got something in common.

17:06.309 --> 17:07.577
Oh, yeah.

17:07.610 --> 17:09.579
And what would that be?

17:09.612 --> 17:10.313
Bobby and I used
to be partners.

17:10.347 --> 17:12.582
Juarez,
you see what a big shot

17:12.615 --> 17:14.351
my ex-partner is?

17:14.384 --> 17:15.518
Hey, can I get a picture?
Huh?

17:15.552 --> 17:17.487
You know, on account
of you being

17:17.520 --> 17:18.755
a celebrity detective and all.

17:18.788 --> 17:20.657
That's a phone, Bobby.

17:20.690 --> 17:22.359
It's got a camera in there.
Where you been?

17:22.392 --> 17:25.262
Me? Been in federal maximum
security prison.

17:25.295 --> 17:27.764
[Laughter]

17:27.797 --> 17:29.799
Come here.

17:29.832 --> 17:31.601
Charlie Crews.

17:31.634 --> 17:33.370
Does it bother you that he spent
all that time in the joint?

17:33.403 --> 17:35.438
And what does that do
to a guy's head?

17:35.472 --> 17:36.839
I'm just saying, you sure
he's gonna be there

17:36.873 --> 17:38.275
when you go through a door?

17:38.308 --> 17:40.510
Does it bother you
that your pal, Stark,

17:40.543 --> 17:42.979
let his partner go down
for a crime he didn't do?

17:43.012 --> 17:45.982
I mean,
I'm just saying.

17:46.015 --> 17:48.551
Do I feel bad
about what happened?

17:48.585 --> 17:50.453
Yeah, I feel bad.

17:50.487 --> 17:52.455
Do I feel guilty?
No.

17:52.489 --> 17:54.457
'Cause I did my job.

17:54.491 --> 17:57.494
There's an investigation,
and then there's a trial.

17:57.527 --> 17:59.228
That's the way it works.

18:02.665 --> 18:05.402
You wanted to see me?

18:05.435 --> 18:06.636
Yeah, your parents missed you
last night

18:06.669 --> 18:08.338
at the Wednesday night dinner,
Dani, you should come back.

18:08.371 --> 18:10.039
Oh, maybe my mom did,

18:10.072 --> 18:12.309
but I don't think
my dad missed me much.

18:12.342 --> 18:13.276
He's not so bad.

18:13.310 --> 18:14.644
I sat in a car with your dad
for three years,

18:14.677 --> 18:15.912
and I came out alive.

18:15.945 --> 18:18.348
Partners aren't parents,
lieutenant.

18:22.352 --> 18:24.354
So, you've been working
the program, Dani?

18:24.387 --> 18:25.955
Is this where
I pee in a cup?

18:25.988 --> 18:27.023
No, this is where you tell me

18:27.056 --> 18:28.325
if you've been
working the program.

18:28.358 --> 18:30.727
Yeah...

18:30.760 --> 18:32.495
I've been working
the program.

18:34.096 --> 18:36.499
Good.

18:36.533 --> 18:38.668
It was a tough draw
getting a new partner.

18:38.701 --> 18:40.370
I'm just a lucky girl,
I guess.

18:40.403 --> 18:42.405
Dani, you know why
you got Crews.

18:42.439 --> 18:45.375
Because I messed up.

18:45.408 --> 18:46.443
You know, I'm at the bottom
of the list,

18:46.476 --> 18:48.077
and there's not a--

18:48.110 --> 18:50.079
there's not a whole lot
I can do about that.

18:50.112 --> 18:52.081
What if there was something
you could do about it?

18:52.114 --> 18:54.083
How come
we're talking about this?

18:54.116 --> 18:56.486
Why did he come back
to the force?

18:56.519 --> 18:57.520
That's not my job
to ask, L.T.

18:57.554 --> 19:01.391
Crews is gonna be trouble.

19:01.424 --> 19:02.459
He got screwed.
He's back to get even.

19:02.492 --> 19:03.626
He's a cop.

19:03.660 --> 19:04.761
Because of his settlement.

19:04.794 --> 19:05.695
You're a cop
because of your work.

19:05.728 --> 19:09.832
You know, I was wondering
who it would be,

19:09.866 --> 19:12.535
who they would send.

19:12.569 --> 19:15.338
And I just kept thinking,

19:15.372 --> 19:17.006
"Oh, you're being paranoid
about this."

19:17.039 --> 19:19.108
Remember how paranoid
I used to get, L.T.?

19:19.141 --> 19:21.578
You don't have
to go to prison to eat crap.

19:21.611 --> 19:24.013
I eat it every day
of my career.

19:24.046 --> 19:25.982
It would be nice if you could
keep your head down

19:26.015 --> 19:27.450
and work the job.

19:27.484 --> 19:30.353
The world
isn't nice like that.

19:30.387 --> 19:31.554
This could be good
for you, Dani.

19:31.588 --> 19:33.423
You're his superior,
and you're responsible

19:33.456 --> 19:35.825
for his supervision
and actions.

19:35.858 --> 19:37.827
He gets jammed up,
I get jammed up?

19:37.860 --> 19:40.029
Has he done anything
that would cause him

19:40.062 --> 19:42.098
to be removed from duty?

19:52.542 --> 19:54.744
He alerted a suspect
that a police search

19:54.777 --> 19:56.446
was about to happen.

20:00.049 --> 20:02.385
And Detective Crews
apparently...

20:05.522 --> 20:07.724
Allowed the suspect to dispose

20:07.757 --> 20:09.426
of a quantity of marijuana,

20:09.459 --> 20:10.927
to flush it down the toilet

20:10.960 --> 20:13.129
just prior to the search.

20:16.165 --> 20:20.036
[Giggles]

20:20.069 --> 20:21.037
How long have
you lived here?

20:21.070 --> 20:22.071
Four months.

20:22.104 --> 20:24.106
When is all
your furniture coming?

20:24.140 --> 20:25.508
This is
all my furniture.

20:25.542 --> 20:28.077
[Laughter]

20:28.110 --> 20:30.012
Man:
Hey, Charlie!

20:30.046 --> 20:31.814
Charlie, I need you
to sign something.

20:31.848 --> 20:33.149
Not now, Ted.

20:33.182 --> 20:34.884
I need you to sign this.
Look, hey.

20:34.917 --> 20:36.819
You were the one that said
you wanted this orange grove.

20:36.853 --> 20:37.920
If you changed your mind,

20:37.954 --> 20:39.556
I would be happy
to unwind the deal,

20:39.589 --> 20:40.623
my friend--
Ted, not now.

20:40.657 --> 20:42.525
I'm, uh, I'm--I'm meditating.

20:44.026 --> 20:45.562
Oh.

20:45.595 --> 20:48.798
Well, that sounds...

20:48.831 --> 20:49.966
Peaceful.

20:49.999 --> 20:51.768
Uh, all right.

20:51.801 --> 20:53.970
I'm...

20:54.003 --> 20:56.072
[Giggles]

20:56.105 --> 20:59.208
Hey, Ted, the orange grove deal
includes the tractor, right?

20:59.241 --> 21:00.810
The big red one?

21:00.843 --> 21:03.980
Yeah, Charlie, it includes
the big red tractor.

21:04.013 --> 21:05.648
Who's that?

21:05.682 --> 21:07.016
Do you read Forbes?

21:07.049 --> 21:08.951
I wasn't very good at prison.

21:08.985 --> 21:12.021
Interviewer:
You were in
for a white-collar crime?

21:12.054 --> 21:14.624
Insider trading.
Yeah.

21:14.657 --> 21:17.994
Charlie saved my life in there,

21:18.027 --> 21:19.962
and so now I handle
his settlement money.

21:19.996 --> 21:22.799
Interviewer:
And you live in his garage?

21:22.832 --> 21:25.535
I live in a room
above his garage.

21:36.679 --> 21:38.247
Do you wanna know
my name?

21:38.280 --> 21:39.616
If I wanted
to know your name,

21:39.649 --> 21:42.552
I would have asked you
for it.

21:42.585 --> 21:44.921
So that means you're
not gonna call?

21:44.954 --> 21:46.155
I can't call
if I don't know your name,

21:46.188 --> 21:48.491
now, can I?

21:48.525 --> 21:50.993
I.M. Stands for instant message.

21:51.027 --> 21:52.629
I know that.

21:52.662 --> 21:53.730
You can't trace an I.M.

21:53.763 --> 21:55.097
Detective, I know that too.

21:56.031 --> 21:57.766
You know we have to see her.

21:57.799 --> 21:59.601
Because it went
so well last time?

21:59.635 --> 22:01.102
I'll be better this time.
You're not gonna talk
this time.

22:01.136 --> 22:02.037
That's what I mean by better.

22:02.070 --> 22:03.439
Look, I know the deal
with your ex-wife,

22:03.472 --> 22:04.706
all right, it's no secret.

22:04.740 --> 22:05.941
So just tell me

22:05.974 --> 22:08.143
that we're gonna go see Alyssa
Gibney because of the case,

22:08.176 --> 22:11.112
and not because of something
that you're working through.

22:11.146 --> 22:14.650
I'm working through the case.

22:14.683 --> 22:17.018
She doesn't want to see you.

22:17.052 --> 22:18.920
Uh, does she want
to see anybody?

22:18.954 --> 22:20.789
She won't come downstairs.

22:20.822 --> 22:22.524
She won't look at her daughter
or talk to her husband.

22:22.558 --> 22:25.627
I'll tell her
you tried to stop us.

22:25.661 --> 22:27.496
[Housekeeper speaking Spanish]

22:37.072 --> 22:38.807
My husband told me
about you.

22:38.840 --> 22:44.680
A cop in jail
all those years.

22:44.713 --> 22:47.716
How did you go on living?

22:47.749 --> 22:49.985
How did you
get past it?

22:50.018 --> 22:54.089
Well, I could tell you
you're already past it.

22:54.122 --> 22:57.192
I could tell you this moment
is your life.

22:57.225 --> 22:59.595
I could tell you
you have a husband and child

22:59.628 --> 23:01.630
who need you.

23:01.663 --> 23:03.699
None of that means anything,
does it?

23:03.732 --> 23:07.669
So tell me something
that means something.

23:07.703 --> 23:08.804
Tell me anything

23:08.837 --> 23:10.906
that means something.

23:20.749 --> 23:23.619
The man who killed
your son is out there.

23:23.652 --> 23:25.987
Right now.

23:26.021 --> 23:28.957
Inside this same moment
we are in.

23:28.990 --> 23:33.595
As we sit here,
as I look at you,

23:33.629 --> 23:37.733
the man
who killed John is free.

23:37.766 --> 23:40.201
Now that means something,
doesn't it?

23:40.235 --> 23:43.805
We're pretty sure
someone was running

23:43.839 --> 23:46.207
a scam on your son, Alyssa,

23:46.241 --> 23:49.545
offering to sell him information
about his father's arrest.

23:49.578 --> 23:51.747
About a technicality that could
get his father out of jail.

23:51.780 --> 23:54.583
That's ridiculous.
Mark is guilty.

23:54.616 --> 23:56.585
John knew that.

23:56.618 --> 23:58.153
Even mark will tell you
he's guilty.

23:58.186 --> 24:00.956
And if there was
a technicality,

24:00.989 --> 24:02.691
why go with it to a child?

24:06.194 --> 24:08.997
Because my son...

24:09.030 --> 24:10.666
A child--

24:10.699 --> 24:11.466
would believe it.

24:11.499 --> 24:14.002
Because a child
would wanna believe

24:14.035 --> 24:15.637
he could get his father out.

24:15.671 --> 24:16.638
Because a child--

24:16.672 --> 24:18.607
would pay
to believe it.

24:18.640 --> 24:21.577
We need to know, Alyssa.

24:21.610 --> 24:26.047
John stole that money,
didn't he?

24:26.081 --> 24:28.550
Yes.

24:28.584 --> 24:32.087
I lied to my husband
when I said that John

24:32.120 --> 24:33.822
was with me.

24:33.855 --> 24:38.594
I lied for him
because I loved him.

24:38.627 --> 24:42.297
He'd been through so much
those early years with Mark.

24:42.330 --> 24:46.134
And I--

24:46.167 --> 24:49.705
he's in the same moment
that we're in.

24:49.738 --> 24:53.842
The man who killed my son.

24:53.875 --> 24:55.877
Will you go get him, please?

25:03.318 --> 25:04.720
[Phone ringing]

25:04.753 --> 25:06.988
Yeah.

25:09.758 --> 25:11.226
Uh, it's for you.

25:15.664 --> 25:17.666
[Clearing throat]
Hello?

25:17.699 --> 25:18.934
[Woman on phone]
Charlie?

25:18.967 --> 25:20.636
You're aware
this isn't my phone?

25:20.669 --> 25:22.170
When you answer your phone,

25:22.203 --> 25:23.672
I'll call you on your phone.

25:23.705 --> 25:24.873
I need to see you.

25:24.906 --> 25:27.809
I'm fighting crime.

25:27.843 --> 25:31.179
Come over tonight.
I'll buy fruit.

25:31.212 --> 25:36.151
I don't exactly
understand you.

25:36.184 --> 25:38.887
You don't have to understand
here to be here.

25:38.920 --> 25:41.823
That's what
I don't understand.

25:41.857 --> 25:44.392
What was Crews like before?

25:44.425 --> 25:47.162
Basic by-the-book cop.
You know.

25:47.195 --> 25:50.265
Looking for his 20
and his pension.

25:50.298 --> 25:52.233
Why?
What's he like now?

26:03.111 --> 26:05.180
You wanna find out
about somebody,

26:05.213 --> 26:06.381
all you have
to do is Google.

26:06.414 --> 26:09.284
I Google myself
all the time.

26:09.317 --> 26:11.720
Google the kid's dad,
Mark Rawls.

26:15.190 --> 26:17.959
Wow.

26:17.993 --> 26:19.861
Well, that's more than enough
to work a scam on a kid.

26:19.895 --> 26:22.297
Google me.

26:22.330 --> 26:24.165
You want to see me?

26:24.199 --> 26:26.434
You don't wanna see that,
Charlie.

26:26.467 --> 26:27.669
Do it.

26:27.703 --> 26:30.305
Do it.

26:39.280 --> 26:41.182
Prison guard:
Get on the floor, convict!

26:41.216 --> 26:44.185
Let's go!
Keep it down!

26:47.989 --> 26:50.125
Inmate:
Cut him!

26:50.158 --> 26:51.993
Inmate #2:
Hey, yo, you better check!

26:52.027 --> 26:53.695
Inmate #3:
Slice him open!

26:53.729 --> 26:55.731
Inmate #2:
Get him on the floor!
Come on!

26:55.764 --> 26:58.333
[Voices echoing]

27:03.739 --> 27:06.341
Your father's been calling me.

27:06.374 --> 27:08.409
Twice today.

27:08.443 --> 27:10.045
Three times yesterday.

27:10.078 --> 27:11.046
Do you want
some melon?

27:11.079 --> 27:13.849
It's very fresh and juicy.

27:13.882 --> 27:16.017
Are you not talking
about this?

27:16.051 --> 27:17.819
I'd ask you to address
all your questions to my lawyer.

27:17.853 --> 27:19.287
I am your lawyer.

27:19.320 --> 27:21.356
Your father
is getting married.

27:21.389 --> 27:23.458
No.
He's getting remarried.

27:23.491 --> 27:24.993
He wants you to come.

27:25.026 --> 27:27.028
His bride to be
is eight years old.

27:27.062 --> 27:30.098
Either way.
I don't have a date.

27:30.131 --> 27:33.234
From what I hear,
you have plenty of dates.

27:35.203 --> 27:37.305
Charlie.

27:37.338 --> 27:39.140
Please call your father.

27:39.174 --> 27:40.942
If only so he will stop
calling me.

27:40.976 --> 27:44.079
My father
is getting remarried

27:44.112 --> 27:47.115
to an eight-year-old
because my mother is dead.

27:47.148 --> 27:50.318
My mother is dead
because he killed her.

27:50.351 --> 27:53.354
He killed her when he
wouldn't let her come see me.

27:53.388 --> 27:56.124
No zen for daddy?

27:56.157 --> 27:58.794
No zen for daddy.

28:06.201 --> 28:09.270
Hey.
Where'd you go?

28:09.304 --> 28:11.072
I'm still here.

28:16.077 --> 28:18.013
Do you ever think
that no one

28:18.046 --> 28:21.382
will ever understand
what we did?

28:21.416 --> 28:24.152
What you and I came through?

28:24.185 --> 28:27.422
Do you ever think

28:27.455 --> 28:29.925
that the world is now
you and me in one place,

28:29.958 --> 28:31.392
everyone else in another?

28:34.095 --> 28:36.998
Sorry.

28:37.032 --> 28:38.800
I'm sorry.
That's stupid.

28:41.236 --> 28:43.471
I think that all the time.

28:57.552 --> 29:00.321
It's late.

29:00.355 --> 29:01.857
I should go.

29:04.325 --> 29:06.061
Yeah.

29:12.868 --> 29:14.836
I'm not attached to this car.

29:14.870 --> 29:17.072
I am not attached
to this car.

29:17.105 --> 29:21.009
[Bentley sound system]
Call from Dani Reese.

29:21.042 --> 29:22.243
Hello?

29:22.277 --> 29:23.544
[Reese on speakerphone]
Hello.

29:23.578 --> 29:24.846
Crews, you there?

29:24.880 --> 29:26.181
Reese?
Am I talking to you?

29:26.214 --> 29:27.315
What do you mean
are you talking to me?

29:27.348 --> 29:28.449
You're talkin' to me.

29:28.483 --> 29:29.985
But how am I talking to you?

29:30.018 --> 29:30.886
Crews!

29:30.919 --> 29:32.387
We got a hit
off the finger you dug up.

29:32.420 --> 29:33.855
A junkie named Lonnie Garth.

29:33.889 --> 29:35.857
He's got no known address,
but he hangs out

29:35.891 --> 29:37.292
at those crack houses downtown.

29:37.325 --> 29:41.997
I'm sending you his mug shot
right now.

29:42.030 --> 29:42.797
To my house?

29:42.830 --> 29:44.933
Reese:
To your phone.

29:47.335 --> 29:48.503
[Chuckles]

29:48.536 --> 29:49.938
It's like--

29:49.971 --> 29:50.738
Reese:
Living in the future?

29:50.771 --> 29:52.307
Actually,
I thought about that,

29:52.340 --> 29:54.242
and it turns out
there really is no future

29:54.275 --> 29:55.410
or past either.

29:55.443 --> 29:58.479
Just now.
And n--

29:58.513 --> 30:00.581
and of course now.

30:00.615 --> 30:02.617
Reese? Reese?

30:06.274 --> 30:07.175
[Man on police radio]
All units. All units.

30:07.208 --> 30:07.842
Suspect located
at 5th and main.

30:07.875 --> 30:11.246
All units. All units.

30:11.279 --> 30:14.249
Why'd you
become a cop again?

30:14.282 --> 30:17.285
When I was doing all that time,
I always thought,

30:17.318 --> 30:19.154
inside me I'm still a cop.

30:19.187 --> 30:20.555
It's what I held on to.

30:20.588 --> 30:23.291
Wow, that sounds like
a lot of crap.

30:23.324 --> 30:24.592
A lot of life
is a lot of crap.

30:24.625 --> 30:26.627
This is command--

30:28.296 --> 30:29.397
well, if I'm in
all those years,

30:29.430 --> 30:31.399
I'm just thinking
about one thing.

30:31.432 --> 30:33.268
Was I set up
for that murder?

30:35.503 --> 30:37.205
Is that what
you'd be thinking?

30:37.238 --> 30:38.339
Yeah.

30:38.373 --> 30:39.174
That and what I'd do

30:39.207 --> 30:41.109
once I found the guys
that set me up.

30:41.142 --> 30:42.110
You ever think
about any of that?

30:42.143 --> 30:43.178
Nope.

30:43.211 --> 30:44.179
I'm thinking about finding

30:44.212 --> 30:46.147
a nine-fingered crackhead.

30:48.516 --> 30:50.418
[Quick breaths]

30:53.254 --> 30:55.256
Lonnie Garth:
I can see you, devils!

30:55.290 --> 30:57.258
I know you come to get me

30:57.292 --> 30:58.459
for what happened
to that kid.

30:58.913 --> 30:59.880
Lonnie Garth?

30:59.914 --> 31:01.716
Devils know my name.

31:01.749 --> 31:03.951
You need to come out here,
so we can arrest you for murder.

31:03.984 --> 31:05.753
I never ever killed that kid!

31:05.786 --> 31:09.223
Arthur did!
Arthur killed that kid!

31:11.125 --> 31:12.627
[Phone rings on tv]

31:12.660 --> 31:13.728
Good morning!

31:13.761 --> 31:16.063
Good morning.
Did you just wake up?

31:16.096 --> 31:18.165
Garth:
That Arthur,
he just wanted the money,

31:18.198 --> 31:20.535
but the kid,
he wouldn't give it to him.

31:20.568 --> 31:23.771
He just started yelling,
so Arthur shot him!

31:23.804 --> 31:25.906
And his dog wouldn't stop
yelling at me,

31:25.940 --> 31:28.609
and it took my finger!

31:28.643 --> 31:30.545
Arthur just wanted the money!

31:30.578 --> 31:32.146
Reese:
Arthur have a last name?

31:32.179 --> 31:33.748
Arthur killed that kid!

31:33.781 --> 31:35.750
But I watched--

31:35.783 --> 31:39.086
I watched Arthur kill that kid,
and I didn't stop him!

31:39.119 --> 31:41.255
I watched Arthur kill that kid,

31:41.288 --> 31:42.557
and I didn't stop him!

31:46.827 --> 31:48.596
I've been waiting for you!

31:48.629 --> 31:50.030
[Cocks rifle]

31:51.632 --> 31:54.602
[Reese grunts]

31:57.738 --> 31:58.673
Reese?

31:58.706 --> 32:00.040
I'm okay!

32:00.074 --> 32:01.842
I'm okay.
I'm not shot.

32:14.288 --> 32:15.990
[Grunts]

32:27.735 --> 32:29.737
Uh, I'm goin' now.

32:34.975 --> 32:37.244
I'm going--
I'm going now.

32:39.780 --> 32:41.782
I never ever killed that kid.

32:41.816 --> 32:45.119
[Pained moans]

32:45.152 --> 32:47.922
I'm going.
I'm going now.

32:50.157 --> 32:53.227
[Whispers]
It was just a bad dream.

32:53.260 --> 32:55.295
Go back to sleep.

33:09.209 --> 33:11.612
Reese?

33:11.646 --> 33:12.847
Reese!

33:17.785 --> 33:19.219
Oh, God.
Get it off me.

33:19.253 --> 33:20.888
Drugs.

33:20.921 --> 33:22.389
Oh, God.
Help me.

33:22.422 --> 33:24.358
Please, please, please,
turn the water on.

33:24.391 --> 33:25.893
Turn the damn water on!

33:25.926 --> 33:28.729
Crews!

33:29.797 --> 33:32.700
Oh! Oh!

33:32.733 --> 33:35.202
[Gasping]

33:40.708 --> 33:42.843
[Whispering]
Yeah.

34:00.728 --> 34:03.197
Hey, you wanna talk
about what happened back there?

34:03.230 --> 34:05.099
The drugs?
The shower?

34:07.034 --> 34:08.703
Well...

34:08.736 --> 34:10.871
We don't have
to talk about it.

34:10.905 --> 34:15.042
We never have
to talk about it.

34:15.075 --> 34:16.276
You know, he said
he never killed that kid.

34:16.310 --> 34:17.978
Reese:
Do we believe that?

34:18.012 --> 34:18.846
He seem like
the kinda guy

34:18.879 --> 34:21.081
who could run
a complicated I.M. scam?

34:21.115 --> 34:23.718
No, he didn't.

34:23.751 --> 34:26.220
He said a guy named Arthur
killed the kid.

34:26.253 --> 34:28.856
Okay, so then how would Arthur
get a hold of

34:28.889 --> 34:31.091
John Gibney's screen name?

34:31.125 --> 34:32.927
There's a directory for
the parents in the Scout troop.

34:32.960 --> 34:35.696
Let's go see if there are
any parents named Arthur.

34:37.164 --> 34:39.399
Arthur Tins, a dad
in the Scout troop,

34:39.433 --> 34:41.168
served two years
for credit card scams,

34:41.201 --> 34:42.803
paroled six months ago.

34:42.837 --> 34:44.138
Hey, Arthur.

34:45.439 --> 34:47.074
How you doin'?

34:47.107 --> 34:48.675
Good.

34:55.249 --> 34:57.384
Why would you show me that?

34:57.417 --> 34:58.786
Does it make you uncomfortable?

34:58.819 --> 35:00.988
No, it makes me sad.

35:01.021 --> 35:04.458
I have a child of my own.

35:04.491 --> 35:08.028
Wait, I know that boy.

35:08.062 --> 35:09.363
He's in my son's troop.

35:09.396 --> 35:11.832
His name is, um,
John something.

35:11.866 --> 35:12.833
John Gibney.

35:12.867 --> 35:13.901
Yeah.

35:13.934 --> 35:15.702
Yeah.
Say his name.

35:18.138 --> 35:20.207
No, I don't think I'll do that.

35:20.240 --> 35:23.110
Next time I ask,
you will.

35:23.143 --> 35:25.012
Reese:
John figured out
you were full of crap.

35:25.045 --> 35:26.380
You had nothing
to free his dad,

35:26.413 --> 35:28.983
but he wouldn't tell you
where the money was,

35:29.016 --> 35:30.217
so you killed him.

35:30.250 --> 35:33.087
By now you've searched my house,
my office, and my computer.

35:33.120 --> 35:37.091
And I know that you have found
nothing at my house,

35:37.124 --> 35:41.328
in my office...
Or on my computer.

35:41.361 --> 35:45.099
Aren't you that cop that spent
all that time in jail?

35:45.132 --> 35:46.867
That must have sucked.

35:46.901 --> 35:49.003
Lonnie Garth said you killed
that kid, Arthur.

35:50.270 --> 35:52.106
You kinda lost it
when he wouldn't pay up.

35:52.139 --> 35:54.208
Lonnie Garth
the dead crackhead?

35:54.241 --> 35:55.542
You're going
to court with that?

35:55.575 --> 35:57.812
We're curious
about the phone calls

35:57.845 --> 36:00.214
between your client
and Lonnie Garth.

36:00.247 --> 36:02.116
What's it like being famous?

36:02.149 --> 36:04.084
A record of those phone calls
proves nothing.

36:04.118 --> 36:05.419
We are done here.

36:09.189 --> 36:10.490
Maybe he can explain the calls,

36:10.524 --> 36:12.026
maybe he can't.

36:12.059 --> 36:12.993
The fact remains
that your client

36:13.027 --> 36:15.062
has been communicating
with a known felon.

36:15.095 --> 36:16.396
A parole violation?

36:16.430 --> 36:18.132
That's what you bring to me?

36:18.165 --> 36:19.967
A parole violation?

36:20.000 --> 36:21.168
What does that carry,
like, a year?

36:21.201 --> 36:23.003
I do that in my sleep.

36:23.037 --> 36:24.138
A year
for killing a kid.

36:29.509 --> 36:31.378
I need a drink.

36:31.411 --> 36:33.413
I know something better.

36:37.451 --> 36:38.953
Mango?

36:38.986 --> 36:40.554
It's okay.

36:40.587 --> 36:43.090
This came all the way
from Guatemala,

36:43.123 --> 36:45.492
and now it's right here
in this cup.

36:45.525 --> 36:46.560
It's all connected, Reese.

36:46.593 --> 36:48.462
What is?

36:48.495 --> 36:50.164
It is.

36:50.197 --> 36:51.165
Mm.

36:51.198 --> 36:52.366
That's zen.

36:52.399 --> 36:53.500
Is it?

36:53.533 --> 36:55.034
That's zen too,
isn't it?

36:55.040 --> 36:56.025
Is it?

36:56.036 --> 36:58.973
Say "is it" one more time,
and I'll shoot you.

37:02.542 --> 37:05.345
[Prison guards muttering]

37:08.482 --> 37:12.552
Don't you two ever give up?

37:12.586 --> 37:13.921
Crews:
Hey, Detective Reese,

37:13.954 --> 37:15.255
isn't that Mark Rawls
over there?

37:15.289 --> 37:19.459
Reese:
I think you're right,
Detective Crews.

37:19.493 --> 37:21.428
Hey, uh, you know Mark Rawls,
don't you, Arthur?

37:21.461 --> 37:24.564
You told his son you could get
him out of jail,

37:24.598 --> 37:25.565
then you broke
his son's heart.

37:25.599 --> 37:26.600
Then you killed him.

37:26.633 --> 37:28.402
I'm gonna need
protective lockup.

37:28.435 --> 37:29.436
For a parole violation?

37:29.469 --> 37:32.072
[Laughs]
You're only here for a year.

37:32.106 --> 37:33.373
You can do that
in your sleep.

37:37.477 --> 37:39.346
Send me somewhere now,

37:39.379 --> 37:41.515
and I'll--and I'll--
and I'll talk.

37:41.548 --> 37:42.582
Start talkin' now.

37:42.616 --> 37:45.519
I killed the kid.
I killed--

37:45.552 --> 37:47.187
Arthur.

37:47.221 --> 37:48.288
Say his name.

37:48.322 --> 37:49.957
John gibney.

37:49.990 --> 37:51.325
I killed John Gibney.

37:51.358 --> 37:53.027
What was that, Arthur?
I didn't catch it.

37:53.060 --> 37:54.628
John Gibney.
I killed John Gibney.

37:54.661 --> 37:56.196
Why?

37:56.230 --> 37:57.231
Because he saw my face.

37:57.684 --> 37:58.685
Lonnie always
got the money,

37:58.718 --> 37:59.486
but the kid
wouldn't give it to him,

37:59.519 --> 38:01.321
so Lonnie brought
the kid to me.

38:01.355 --> 38:02.556
And John wouldn't give you
the money either.

38:02.589 --> 38:03.890
Guard:
Let's go.

38:06.560 --> 38:08.061
Lonnie was supposed
to get the money.

38:08.094 --> 38:10.697
He wasn't supposed to see me.
He saw my face.

38:18.738 --> 38:20.574
It is all connected.

38:35.689 --> 38:36.823
I thought you'd want
to know the department

38:36.856 --> 38:38.024
is prepared to go ahead

38:38.057 --> 38:39.693
with the complaint
against Crews.

38:39.726 --> 38:41.595
What complaint is that?

38:41.628 --> 38:43.930
That you saw him
allow a suspect

38:43.963 --> 38:45.899
to flush a controlled substance
down the toilet.

38:45.932 --> 38:48.935
But I didn't see that.

38:48.968 --> 38:51.905
I said that he apparently
flushed those drugs

38:51.938 --> 38:53.873
because I did not see
that happen.

38:53.907 --> 38:56.376
I mean, I don't know
exactly what happened.

38:56.410 --> 38:58.111
I'm not sure
I understand you, Dani.

39:00.714 --> 39:03.717
You don't have
to understand here to be here.

39:03.750 --> 39:05.385
Is this a problem for you

39:05.419 --> 39:06.553
because of your own history
with drugs?

39:06.586 --> 39:07.887
I went to rehab for that.

39:07.921 --> 39:08.855
Yeah.

39:08.888 --> 39:10.624
I've been clean for 21 months.

39:10.657 --> 39:12.826
Even with rehab,
the department doesn't have

39:12.859 --> 39:16.095
to keep you on the job.

39:16.129 --> 39:17.897
You didn't get
a settlement, Dani.

39:19.766 --> 39:21.635
So the next time Crews
does something...

39:23.002 --> 39:25.805
I need to make sure
I do see it.

39:27.741 --> 39:33.413
Life was his sentence,
and life is what he got back.

39:33.447 --> 39:35.449
Interviewer:
What do you think
he should do with that life?

39:37.884 --> 39:42.121
That would be up to him.

